      "content": "that's really helpful, thanks. one thing my students struggle with is when the opposition calls these arguments \"xenophobic\" or \"hateful.\" it's a tough label to shake in a debate. how can they respond to that accusation while still holding their ground on the necessity of strict enforcement? is there a way to frame it so they can show their position is based on policy and legal structure rather than animosity?",
